name: Brazilian Virgin Remy 14 Piece Clip In Extensions (16", 20", or 22")
description:
Virgin Remy Clip In Extensions come with 14 pieces of extensions. This gives you the ability to make your extensions look as thin or thick as you prefer. The 14 piece set weighs at 140g.

The Virgin Remy Clip In Extensions can be colored, straightened, curled and/or washed. They are just like virgin hair extensions except they have been processed to the preferred colored. 

Lengths: 16", 20" or 22"
Style: Straight
Type: Virgin Remy
# of Pieces in Clip In Set: 14 pieces
Color: Optional
Life Expectancy: 6months+ if properly taken care of

name: 5A Virgin Brazilian Curly 3 Bundle Packages
description:
Brazilian hair is the most sold and popular virgin hair on the market today. It originates in Brazil of South America. Brazilian hair is soft, luxurious, durable and known for its density (or thickness). Brazilian hair is not extremely thick nor is it too thin. It’s the perfect amount of hair. Brazilian hair comes in natural black and is the easiest type of virgin hair to blend in with all hair ethnicities and textures. No virgin hair is excessively shiny. They all have a low-medium luster but Brazilian seems to have a very nice natural shine to it; medium luster. When it comes to curls, Brazilian hair will hold curls longer. After a wash and air dry, straight virgin hair tends to have a slight wave. This can be fixed with a use of a straightener. Curly/wavy virgin hair seems to be more curlier and wavier when air dried. If blow drying is a must, use a diffuser on a low heat setting to set curls/waves. DO NOT SCRUNCH CURLY OR WAVY HAIR. Scrunching creates frizz. Brazilian hair is also more unlikely to frizz in humid conditions unlike Indian.

Grade: 5AAAAA 
Lengths: 12"-26" 
Style: Curly 
Type: Brazilian 
# of Bundles in Package: 3 bundles (10.5-12oz of hair) 
Color: Black 
Life Expectancy: At least 1 year if properly taken care of

*12"-16" can probably get away with 2 bundles for a FULL sew in. 3 bundles are recommended. Better to have too much hair than not enough. Plus whatever you don't use, can be used in the next install/touch ups.

**Hair can be colored but is not recommended because it may dry out your hair.
